<p itemprop="description">User focus involves understanding user needs, behaviours, and contexts to design and deliver services that work well for the people who need to use them.</p>

<div class="proficiency-levels">
    <h2>Proficiency Levels</h2>

    <ol class="skill-levels">
        <li>
            <h3>Awareness</h3>
            <p>You can understand the importance of user-centred design and recognise when user needs should influence decisions.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h3>Working</h3>
            <p>You can gather and interpret user feedback, apply user insights to improve services, and advocate for user needs in team discussions.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h3>Practitioner</h3>
            <p>You can lead user-centred design processes, synthesise complex user research into actionable insights, and champion user needs across the organisation.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h3>Expert</h3>
            <p>You can establish user-centred culture and practices, lead user experience strategy, and influence organisational decisions based on deep user insight.</p>
        </li>
    </ol>
</div>

